Cluster-1:High-Value Premium Buyers
  →Customers who spend large amounts regularly
Behavioral Characteristics:-
  purchase premium products
  Loyal to brand
  Prefer high-quality products
Spending Habits:-
  High spending per purchase
  High lifetime value
  Less price 
Demographic Pattern:-
  Age: 30–55
  Higher income groups
Cluster-2: Budget Occasional Shoppers
   →Customers who purchase infrequant and prefer discounts
Behavioral Characteristics:-
   during sales or promotions
   Compare prices before buying
   Low brand 
Spending Habits:-
   Low to medium spending
   Purchase only when necessary
   Prefer budget products
Demographic Pattern:-
  Age: 18–35
  Students
Cluster-3: High-Frequency Low Spenders
     →Customers who shop often but spend small amounts each time
Behavioral Characteristics:-
    visits frequantly
    Purchase small items regularly
Spending Habits:-
   Low purchase value
   High purchase frequency
   Respond well to loyalty programs
Demographic Pattern:-
    Age: 20–40
    Urban customers
    Middle income 
Cluster-4: At-Risk Customers
     →Customers who used to buy but are now inactive.
Behavioral Characteristics:-
     Declining purchase frequency
     Reduced engagement
     May have shifted to competitors
Spending Habits:-
    Previously medium/high spenders
    Recent drop in spending
Demographic Pattern:-
     Age: 30–60
     Previously loyal customer
